    "en": {
      "title": "Police fire tear gas at protesters near parliament entry road",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The police fired tear gas and water cannons at a group of protesters near Diyatha Uyana, close to the parliament entry road this afternoon (July 06).",
        "According to reports, the demonstrators had attempted to advance through the barricades set up by the police.",
        "The protest march is organized by the joint trade unions for the protection of petroleum resources.",
        "As a result, the parliament entry roads from Polduwa Junction and the Japanese Friendship Bridge have been closed for vehicular movement."
      ],
